article.headline: Virginia 76, Oral Roberts 55
article.story: CHARLOTTESVILLE, Va. -- Mike Scott scored 15 points and grabbed 10 rebounds and Sylven Landesberg added 14 points to lead Virginia to a 76-55 win over Oral Roberts in the final states-side game of the Cancun Challenge on Saturday. On Tuesday in Cancun, Mexico, Virginia (3-1) plays Stanford. Oral Roberts (2-2) takes on Sam Houston State. Midway through the second half, Virginia, which led by six at halftime, pulled away with an 11-4 run. Assane Sene, who was suspended for the Cavaliers first three games, scored five points during the spurt. Sene, a 7-footer, finished with eight points and seven rebounds. Back-to-back baskets by Sene and Landesberg gave Virginia a 59-42 lead. Will Sherrill's 3-pointer gave the Cavaliers a 20-point advantage. Kevin Ford led Oral Roberts with 16 points and 10 rebounds. Virginia held the Golden Eagles to 32-percent shooting.
